03/12/2006
TEHRAN, Iran -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan was in Tehran Sunday (December 3rd) for daylong talks on the situation in the Middle East. 
He also planned to discuss measures to boost bilateral relations, regional stability and prosperity.
Pope Benedict XVI, meanwhile, wrapped up his visit to Turkey on Friday with a message of hope. 
"Istanbul is a bridge that unites sides â¦ I hope that this dialogue continues", he said referring to efforts to reconcile differences between the world's major religions. 
(AFP - 03/12/06; AP - 02/12/06)
